  "transliteration": "brahma-bhūtaḥ prasannātmā na śhochati na kāṅkṣhati\nsamaḥ sarveṣhu bhūteṣhu mad-bhaktiṁ labhate parām",
  "translation": "One who is realized as Brahman becomes joyful, free from lamentation and desire, equal toward all beings, and attains supreme devotion.",
